  <p>Welcome to my personal web hub.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>I am Peng Lin, or bryan. I am from Nanjing, China. Currently I am a Postdoc Associate at <a href="http://www.mit.edu">Massachusetts Institiute of Technology (MIT)</a>. I got my PhD from <a href="www.umass.edu">University of Massachusetts Amherst (UMass)</a> in Electrical Engingineering. My research focuses on <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neuromorphic_engineering">Neuromorphic Computing</a>. This is an entirely new computing architecture that uses emerging nanoelectronic devices such as <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Memristor">Memristor</a> to form highly parallel matrix multiplication networks to operate neural networks on site, similarly like what happens in a brain. We hope the new system can provide the breakthroughs in speed and energy efficiency and overcome the hardware bottleneck of current artificial intelligence systems.</p>

